tool.name: 2DFET
tool.title: 2DFET
tool.about: 2D FET - a numerical simulator for two-dimensional (2D) FET. Both n-type and p-type channel FETs, for a variety of monolayer 2D materials, including MoS2, MoSe2, MoTe2, WS2, and Black Phorsphorene (BP), can be simulated. Transistor characteristics at both the ballistic limit and with scattering can be assessed.

about.label: Channel Material
about.description: Determine the channel material of 2D FET Choose the monolayer 2D material as the channel material of 2D FET

about.label: CMOS type
about.description: Determine n-type or p-type 2D FET Choose either n-type or p-type channel

about.label: channel direction
about.description: Choose the cystaline direction along the transistor channel. x-direction and y-direction are mutually perpendicular

about.label: transport model
about.description: ballistic transport or with scattering in the channel

about.label: Gate length [nm]
about.description: Gate length (only used for transport model with scattering)

about.label: scattering mfp [nm]
about.description: scattering mean free path (mfp) in transistor channel.(only used for transport model with scattering)

about.label: Threshold Voltage
about.description: The approximate threshold voltage specified here is a way to set the transistor off-current.

about.label: Gate Control Parameter
about.description:
The gate control parameter, alphaG, is the gate capacitance divided by the sum of the gate, source and drain capacitances. It controls the subthreshold swing according to S = (2.3kT/q)/alphaG. When alphaG=1 and alphaD=0, there is complete gate control; the subthreshold swing is ideal and drain induced barrier lowering (DIBL) is zero.
Note that the sum of the gate and drain control parameters should be less than or equal to 1.

about.label: Drain Control Parameter
about.description:
The drain control parameter, alphaD, is the drain capacitance divided by the sum of the gate, source and drain capacitances. It controls the drain induced barrier lowering (DIBL) according to DIBL = S * alphaD/(2.3kT/q), where S is the subthreshold swing.
Note that the sum of the gate and drain control parameters shold be less than or equal to 1.

about.label: Ambient Temperature
about.description: Temperature in the environment around the device.

about.label: Initial Gate Voltage
about.description: The simulator sweeps gate voltages. This is the starting gate voltage for the sweep.

about.label: Final Gate Voltage
about.description: The simulator sweeps gate voltages. This is the final gate voltage for the sweep.

about.label: Gate Voltage Bias Points
about.description: Number of bias points for the gate voltage sweep.

about.label: Initial Drain Voltage
about.description: The simulator sweeps drain voltages. This is the starting drain voltage for the sweep.

about.label: Final Drain Voltage
about.description: The simulator sweeps drain voltages. This is the final drain voltage for the sweep.

about.label: Drain Voltage Bias Points
about.description: Number of bias points for the drain voltage sweep.
